# Cursor Rules for WaitLa Digital Marketing Agency Website

## Optimal Tech Stack Recommendation

### Core Framework
**Next.js 14+ (App Router)**
- ✅ Built-in SSR/SSG for optimal SEO
- ✅ Image optimization out of the box
- ✅ API routes for form handling
- ✅ Built-in i18n routing support
- ✅ Automatic code splitting
- ✅ Excellent Lighthouse scores
- ✅ Vercel deployment (zero-config)

**Why Next.js over React/Vue:**
- SEO is critical for agency visibility → SSR/SSG essential
- Performance requirements (<3s load) → Next.js optimizations
- Multilingual routing → Next.js i18n is mature
- Portfolio/content-heavy → SSG perfect for static content

### Language & Type Safety
**TypeScript**
- Type safety for complex portfolio data structures
- Better DX with autocomplete
- Catch errors at build time
- Essential for team collaboration

### Styling
**Tailwind CSS 3+**
- Rapid UI development (matches PRD's modern aesthetic)
- Mobile-first responsive utilities
- Small bundle size with JIT
- Easy customization for brand colors
- Shadcn/ui components (built on Tailwind) for consistent UI

**Why Tailwind over CSS-in-JS:**
- Better performance (no runtime CSS-in-JS overhead)
- Faster development for showcase sites
- Easier to maintain consistent design system
- Better for SSR/SSG

### Animations
**Framer Motion**
- React-friendly API
- Excellent performance with layout animations
- Perfect for scroll animations, hover effects
- Supports reduced motion preferences
- Lightweight compared to GSAP for most use cases

**Consider GSAP if:**
- Complex timeline animations needed
- Advanced scroll-triggered sequences
- Timeline-based video-like animations

### Content Management
**Sanity CMS (Recommended)**
- ✅ Excellent for portfolio/case studies
- ✅ Real-time collaboration
- ✅ Flexible content modeling
- ✅ Built-in image optimization
- ✅ Free tier generous for showcase sites
- ✅ Great developer experience
- ✅ Easy for non-technical team to update content

**Alternative: Contentful**
- More enterprise-focused
- Better for larger teams
- Higher cost for advanced features

**Alternative: Strapi (Self-hosted)**
- Full control over data
- Good if you need custom backend logic
- Requires hosting/maintenance

### Forms & Validation
**React Hook Form**
- Performance (uncontrolled components)
- Minimal re-renders
- Great TypeScript support

**Zod**
- Schema validation
- TypeScript type inference
- Works seamlessly with React Hook Form

**Form Submission:**
- Next.js API routes
- Email service: **Resend** (modern, developer-friendly) or SendGrid
- Database: **Supabase** (PostgreSQL) for contact form submissions + analytics
  - Free tier sufficient for showcase site
  - Built-in auth if needed later
  - Real-time capabilities

### Internationalization
**next-intl**
- Built for Next.js App Router
- Type-safe translations
- SEO-friendly locale routing
- Better than next-i18next for App Router

**Translation Management:**
- Store translations in Sanity CMS or JSON files
- Consider Crowdin/Lokalise if multiple translators

### Icons
**Lucide React**
- Modern, consistent icon set
- Tree-shakeable
- TypeScript support
- Lightweight
- Better than Font Awesome (smaller bundle)

### Image & Media Handling
**Next.js Image Component**
- Automatic optimization
- Lazy loading
- Responsive images
- WebP/AVIF support

**Video:**
- Use HTML5 `<video>` with proper attributes
- Host on Vercel Blob Storage or Cloudflare R2
- Consider Cloudinary for advanced video transformations

### Database & Storage
**Supabase (PostgreSQL)**
- Contact form submissions
- Analytics data (optional)
- Free tier: 500MB database
- Built-in REST API
- Real-time subscriptions if needed

**Alternative: Vercel Postgres**
- Native Next.js integration
- Serverless
- Pay-as-you-go

**File Storage:**
- **Vercel Blob Storage** (images, videos)
- Or **Cloudflare R2** (S3-compatible, cheaper)
- Or **Cloudinary** (advanced image/video transformations)

### Hosting & Deployment
**Vercel (Primary Recommendation)**
- Zero-config Next.js deployment
- Automatic HTTPS
- Global CDN
- Preview deployments
- Analytics included
- Free tier generous for showcase sites

**Alternative: Netlify**
- Similar features to Vercel
- Good Next.js support
- Great for static sites

### Analytics & Monitoring
**Google Analytics 4**
- Required per PRD
- Track conversions, user behavior

**Vercel Analytics**
- Real-time performance metrics
- Web Vitals tracking
- Included with Vercel hosting

**Optional: PostHog or Plausible**
- Privacy-focused alternative
- Better for GDPR compliance

### SEO Tools
**next-seo** or **next-sitemap**
- Generate sitemap.xml
- robots.txt
- Meta tag management

**Schema Markup:**
- Use `next-seo` or manual JSON-LD
- Organization, Service, Review schemas

### Security
**reCAPTCHA v3** or **Turnstile (Cloudflare)**
- Form spam protection
- Better UX than v2

**Honeypot fields**
- Additional spam protection
- No user friction

### Development Tools
**Package Manager:**
- **pnpm** (faster, disk-efficient) or **npm**

**Linting & Formatting:**
- **ESLint** (Next.js config)
- **Prettier** (code formatting)

**Testing (Optional for MVP):**
- **Vitest** (unit tests)
- **Playwright** (E2E tests for critical flows)

### Performance Optimization
**Bundle Analysis:**
- `@next/bundle-analyzer`

**Image Optimization:**
- Next.js Image (automatic)
- Consider **Sharp** for advanced transformations

**Code Splitting:**
- Automatic with Next.js
- Dynamic imports for heavy components

### Recommended Project Structure
```
waitla-website/
├── app/                    # Next.js App Router
│   ├── [locale]/          # i18n routes (en, fr)
│   │   ├── about/
│   │   ├── services/
│   │   ├── portfolio/
│   │   └── contact/
│   ├── api/               # API routes (forms, etc.)
│   └── layout.tsx
├── components/
│   ├── ui/                # Shadcn/ui components
│   ├── sections/          # Page sections
│   └── layout/            # Header, Footer, etc.
├── lib/
│   ├── sanity/            # Sanity client
│   ├── utils.ts
│   └── validations.ts     # Zod schemas
├── public/
│   └── assets/
├── messages/              # i18n translations
│   ├── en.json
│   └── fr.json
└── types/
    └── index.ts
```

